paragraphs.title: 1 - Afficher le nombre d’articles/évènements qu’il y a eu pour chaque triplet (jour, pays de l’évènement, langue de l’article).
paragraphs.text:
%neo4j

MATCH (doc:Document)-[:MENTION]->(e:Event)-[:IN]->(c:Country)
MATCH (doc)-[:ON]->(d:Day)
RETURN DISTINCT COUNT(DISTINCT doc) AS NbDocuments, d.Day AS Date, c.Name AS Country, doc.Language AS Language
ORDER BY NbDocuments DESC

paragraphs.text:
%neo4j

MATCH (e:Event)-[:IN]->(c:Country)
MATCH (e)-[:ON]->(d:Day)
WITH DISTINCT COUNT(DISTINCT e) AS nbEvents, c.Name AS Country, e, substring(d.Id , 0, 4) + '-' + substring(d.Id , 4, 2) + '-' + substring(d.Id , 6, 2) AS Date
MATCH (doc:Document)-[:MENTION]->(e)
RETURN DISTINCT COUNT(DISTINCT doc) AS nbDocuments, nbEvents, Date, Country, COALESCE(doc.Language, "en") AS Language
ORDER BY nbEvents DESC
LIMIT 1000

paragraphs.title: 2 - pour un acteur donné en paramètre, afficher les événements (valeurs de la table events) qui y font référence (dans les derniers 6 mois).
paragraphs.text:
%neo4j
MATCH (a:Actor)
USING INDEX a:Actor(Id)
WHERE a.Id = 'USA'
MATCH (a)-[:SOURCE|TARGET]-(e:Event)-[:ON]->(d:Day)
WHERE d.Id > '20180101'
RETURN e
LIMIT 1000

paragraphs.title: 3 - trouver les sujets (acteurs) qui ont eu le plus d’articles positifs/negatifs pour chaque triplet (mois, pays, langue de l’article).
paragraphs.text:
%neo4j
MATCH (a:Actor)-[:SOURCE|TARGET]-(e:Event)-[:IN]->(c:Country)
MATCH (doc:Document)-[:MENTION]->(e)-[:ON]->(d:Day)
WITH DISTINCT substring(d.Id , 0, 4) + '-' + substring(d.Id , 4, 2) + '-' + substring(d.Id , 6, 2) AS date, c.Name AS country, doc.Language AS language, a AS actor, COLLECT(DISTINCT e) AS events
WITH DISTINCT date, country, language, actor, SIZE(FILTER(e IN events WHERE e.AvgTone > 0)) AS positiveCount
ORDER BY positiveCount DESC
WITH DISTINCT date, country, language, head(COLLECT ({ Actor: actor, PositiveCount: positiveCount })) AS result
RETURN DISTINCT date AS Date, country AS Country, COALESCE(language, "en") AS Language, result.PositiveCount AS PositiveTone

paragraphs.text:
%neo4j
MATCH (a:Actor)-[:SOURCE|TARGET]-(e:Event)-[:IN]->(c:Country)
MATCH (doc:Document)-[:MENTION]->(e)-[:ON]->(d:Day)
WITH DISTINCT substring(d.Id , 0, 4) + '-' + substring(d.Id , 4, 2) + '-' + substring(d.Id , 6, 2) AS date, c.Name AS country, doc.Language AS language, a AS actor, COLLECT(DISTINCT e) AS events
WITH DISTINCT date, country, language, actor, SIZE(FILTER(e IN events WHERE e.AvgTone <= 0)) AS negativeCount
ORDER BY negativeCount DESC
WITH DISTINCT date, country, language, head(COLLECT ({ Actor: actor, NegativeCount: negativeCount })) AS result
RETURN DISTINCT date AS Date, country AS Country, COALESCE(language, "en") AS Language, result.NegativeCount AS NegativeCount

paragraphs.title: 4 - trouver quels sont les acteurs/pays/organisations qui divisent le plus (par exemple ont eu une perception positive dans une partie du globe et une perception negative dans le rest du monde). Permettez une agrégation par jour/mois/annee.
paragraphs.text:
%neo4j
MATCH (a:Actor)-[:SOURCE|TARGET]-(e:Event)-[:ON]->(d:Day)
WITH DISTINCT d.Id AS date, a.Name AS actor, stDev(e.AvgTone) AS std
ORDER BY std DESC
WITH date, head(COLLECT({ Actor: actor, Std: std })) AS raw
WITH date, raw.Std as std, raw.Actor as Actor
RETURN date, avg(std) AS StandardDeviation, Actor
LIMIT 1000

paragraphs.title: Bonus - Vous devez proposer et implementer une fonctionnalité supplémentaire qui nous permettra de mieux comprendre l’évolution des relations entre les différents pa, en étudiant le ton des mentions (positives/negatives) dans les articles médias de chaque pays
paragraphs.text:
%neo4j
//By Document
MATCH (a1:Actor)
USING INDEX a1:Actor(Id)
WHERE a1.Id = 'JOR'
WITH a1
MATCH (a2:Actor)
USING INDEX a2:Actor(Id)
WHERE a2.Id ='ISR'
WITH a2, a1
MATCH (a1)-[:SOURCE|TARGET]-(e:Event)-[:SOURCE|TARGET]-(a2)
MATCH (e)<-[:MENTION]-(doc:Document)-[:ON]->(d:Day)
RETURN avg(doc.Tone) AS Tone,substring(d.Id , 0, 4) + '-' + substring(d.Id , 4, 2) + '-' + substring(d.Id , 6, 2) AS Date
ORDER BY Date
